- DESCRIPTION

Transfers program control to a return address located on the top of the stack. The address is usually placed on the stack by a call instruction, and the return is made to the instruction that follows the CALL instruction.

The optional soruce operand specifies the number of stack bytes to be released after the return address is popped; the default is none. This operand can be used to release parameters from the stack that were passed to the called procedure and are no longer needed. It must be used when the CALL instruction used to switch to a new procedure uses a call gate with a none-zero word count to access the new procedure.
